{
  "stem": "6526.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was one bomb.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then, of course, everybody started to get afraid and to see what we're going to do.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My parents and other people of that age, which they were in their late 40s, early or late 40s, remembered the First World War.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they said that when Germans come in, the first thing, they grabbed men to do work.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what is there to do?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We have to run away.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Being that we had some trucks, my father and my brother and I and some other friends also, we loaded up a truck and we went east, as far as the Russian border, to a city called Mezhirich.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's on the southeast border between Poland and Russia.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We did not hear what had happened to Kaluszyn and that town.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We left about the 7th of July-- of, excuse me-- September.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--about September 7th.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were there until about 10 days until the Russian army came in to Poland and they occupied.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Being that they occupied, we says, no, right now, we're going to go with the Russians back to Kaluszyn.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As we were traveling, not with them, but after that, their military went first, we heard that the Russian supposedly and the Germans had made an agreement that the Russians will be on one side of the Vistula, of the river that divides Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One side is Praga and one side is Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the east side will be for Russians, and the west side will be for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were glad that this is going to be like that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So our town will be under Russian occupation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when we came to a town called Siedlce, which is 33 kilometers from Warsaw, we noticed that the Russian army is coming back.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
